        "title": "2. `providers.py` — pure-logic branches are cheap wins, network crawlers need mocking",
        "content": "\n**Untested, no-HTTP-dependency logic (easiest, highest ROI):**\n- `MadagascarTribune._is_article_link` — 4 independent boolean branches, zero I/O, no excuse to skip\n\n```python\nimport pytest\nfrom providers import MadagascarTribune\n\n@pytest.mark.parametrize(\"href,expected\", [\n    (\"some-article.html\", True),\n    (\"category-.html\", False),          # rubrique convention, not article\n    (\"https://external.com/a.html\", False),\n    (\"/absolute/path.html\", False),\n    (\"_AuthorName,42_.html\", False),    # byline page\n    (\"no-extension\", False),\n    (None, False),\n])\ndef test_is_article_link(href, expected):\n    assert MadagascarTribune._is_article_link(href) is expected\n```\n\n**Untested, HTTP-mocked crawlers:**\n- `MadagascarTribune._discover_categories`: rubrique-id regex extraction, dedup+sort by int, homepage-fetch failure → `[]`\n- `MadagascarTribune.list_article_urls`: pagination stops when a page yields 0 new links; per-category fetch exception breaks that category only (not the whole crawl); redirect URL (`page.url`) used for subsequent pagination\n- `FreeNews.list_article_urls`: pages until empty list; `HTTPError(400)` → stop (past last page); any other `HTTPError` → re-raised (not swallowed) — **this distinction is currently untested and easy to break**\n- `Moov.list_article_urls`: BFS dedup via `queued` set; only `/article/` links enqueued; fetch failure during frontier expansion doesn't stop the whole crawl (`continue`)\n- `PROVIDERS` registry: every entry's `source_name` matches its dict key (a copy-paste bug here silently breaks state/log/data paths)\n\n```python\ndef test_providers_registry_keys_match_source_name():\n    from providers import PROVIDERS\n    for key, cls in PROVIDERS.items():\n        assert cls.source_name == key\n\ndef test_freenews_stops_on_400_but_reraises_other_http_errors():\n    import urllib.error\n    from unittest.mock import patch\n    from providers import FreeNews\n    src = FreeNews()\n    with patch(\"providers.urllib.request.urlopen\",\n               side_effect=urllib.error.HTTPError(\"u\", 400, \"x\", {}, None)):\n        assert list(src.list_article_urls()) == []\n    with patch(\"providers.urllib.request.urlopen\",\n               side_effect=urllib.error.HTTPError(\"u\", 500, \"x\", {}, None)):\n        with pytest.raises(urllib.error.HTTPError):\n            list(src.list_article_urls())\n```\n\n---\n\n",
        "level": 3
      },
