        "title": "3. `models.py` — low risk, but worth a smoke test for defaults",
        "content": "\n```python\nfrom models import Article, SiteSelectors\n\ndef test_article_images_default_factory_is_independent_per_instance():\n    a1 = Article(url=\"a\", title=\"t\", body=\"b\", author=None, published_date=None,\n                 category=None, source=\"s\", scraped_at=\"now\")\n    a2 = Article(url=\"b\", title=\"t\", body=\"b\", author=None, published_date=None,\n                 category=None, source=\"s\", scraped_at=\"now\")\n    a1.images.append(\"x\")\n    assert a2.images == []  # guards against a future `images: list = []` mutable-default regression\n```\n\n---\n\n",
        "level": 3
      },
      {
        "title": "4. `main.py` — CLI argument handling and orchestration untested",
        "content": "\n- `--provider all` expands to every key in `PROVIDERS`, in dict order\n- invalid provider name is rejected by `argparse` (choices)\n- `--limit` default is `10` and is passed through to `crawl()`\n- each provider's `crawl()` is invoked once with `on_save` set\n\n```python\nfrom unittest.mock import patch, MagicMock\nimport sys\nfrom main import main\n\ndef test_main_all_expands_to_every_provider(monkeypatch):\n    fake_source = MagicMock()\n    fake_source.crawl.return_value = []\n    with patch(\"main.PROVIDERS\", {\"a\": MagicMock(return_value=fake_source),\n                                   \"b\": MagicMock(return_value=fake_source)}), \\\n         patch.object(sys, \"argv\", [\"main.py\", \"all\"]):\n        main()\n    assert fake_source.crawl.call_count == 2\n\ndef test_main_passes_limit_through(monkeypatch):\n    fake_source = MagicMock()\n    fake_source.crawl.return_value = []\n    fake_cls = MagicMock(return_value=fake_source)\n    with patch(\"main.PROVIDERS\", {\"a\": fake_cls}), \\\n         patch.object(sys, \"argv\", [\"main.py\", \"a\", \"--limit\", \"5\"]):\n        main()\n    _, kwargs = fake_source.crawl.call_args\n    assert kwargs[\"limit\"] == 5\n```\n\n---\n\n",
        "level": 3
      },
      {
        "title": "5. Integration test gaps",
        "content": "\nThere is no test that exercises a full `crawl()` cycle against a realistic fixture (saved HTML/sitemap XML) end-to-end for at least one real provider (e.g. record a static sitemap + article HTML fixture for `lexpress-mg`, run `crawl(limit=1)` against it via a stubbed `Fetcher`, assert the JSONL/state files produced). This is the one test that would catch selector regressions when a provider's HTML changes — currently the only signal for that is a silent empty-`body`/`None` in production.\n\nAlso missing: a resumability integration test — run `crawl()` twice against the same fixture data and assert the second run saves 0 new articles (proves `seen_urls` + state file wiring works end-to-end, not just in isolation).\n\n---\n\n",
